  "prompt": "Where can I get best quality soft contact lenses in Sydney?",
  "response": "In Sydney, you can find high-quality soft contact lenses at several reputable optometry clinics and optical retailers. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. **Local Optometrists**: Visiting a local optometrist can ensure you receive a proper eye examination and recommendations tailored to your needs. Some well-known optometry clinics include:\n   - **Specsavers**: They have multiple locations and offer a range of contact lenses.\n   - **Graham F. Smith Optometry**: Known for personalized service and quality products.\n\n2. **Specialized Contact Lens Providers**: Some clinics focus specifically on contact lenses and may offer a wider variety of brands and types.\n   - **Contact Lens Specialists**: They can provide in-depth consultations and fitting services.\n\n3. **Optical Chains**: Larger stores often have a good selection of lenses, sometimes at competitive prices.\n   - ** OPSM**: A well-known retailer that offers various brands of contact lenses.\n\n4. **Online Retailers**: If you're looking for convenience, online shops like **Contact Lens Hut** or **Cheaper Eyewear** can provide quality lenses delivered to your door, often at lower prices.\n\n5. **Specialty Stores**: Look for stores that carry premium brands like Acuvue, Air Optix, or Biofinity. They might also provide trial lenses to help you find the right fit.\n\nAlways ensure that you have a valid prescription from an eye care professional before purchasing contact lenses. It's essential for your eye health to receive a proper fitting and to choose lenses that suit your lifestyle.",
